This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on neural machine translation models. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as neural MT models are a type of machine learning model. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the ability of neural MT models to learn and represent language. The paper also mentions the depth of the encoding layer, which suggests it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the quality of the representations through extrinsic part-of-speech and morphological tagging tasks, which could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these tasks are often used in computer vision applications.
